## Description
The **Enrich Analytics (Pweb) **task allows to consolidate the analytics of different, previously identified Pweb delivery procedures (SMS and email) under a single code, correlating them to the same communications campaign and thus avoiding dispersion of information.

> Note

For the correct generation of all the events required for the extraction of an analytics report, the workflow for a Pweb application must include the Enrich Analytics (Pweb) task, properly configured according to the documents to be produced and the selected delivery channel.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

This task may be added after a [Publish Documents (Pweb)](/doxee-platform/docs/publish-documents-pweb-batch-workflow-task-reference) task and before a Delivery ([FTP](/doxee-platform/docs/deliver-files-ftp-batch-workflow-task-reference), [Email](/doxee-platform/docs/deliver-emails-batch-workflow-task-reference) or [SMS](/doxee-platform/docs/deliver-sms-batch-workflow-task-reference)) task in a workflow; for example:

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,) 

> Warning

This task only works if connected to a branch with the **Assign lot **option enabled; otherwise, the task ends in error. For example:

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,) For more information, see: [Doxee Platform Batch Workflows - Designing a Workflow](/doxee-platform/docs/doxee-platform-batch-workflows-designing-a-workflow).

## Configuration
**![](data:image/png;base64,)**

- In the **Alias **field, enter the name of the task that will be displayed in the workflow.

- From the **Channel **drop-down menu, select the type of delivery channel used in the workflow and connected in output to the Enrich Analytics task:

**SMS ** if the following task in the workflow is the [Deliver SMS](/doxee-platform/docs/deliver-emails-batch-workflow-task-reference) task

- **Email ** if the following task in the workflow is the [Deliver Emails](/doxee-platform/docs/deliver-emails-batch-workflow-task-reference) task

- **FTP ** if the following task in the workflow is the [Deliver Files (FTP)](/doxee-platform/docs/deliver-files-ftp-batch-workflow-task-reference) task

- **None ***(currently not supported)*

> Warning

If the workflow includes several delivery steps (Email, SMS, FTP), they must refer to the same Lot ID but different Shipment IDs.

This means that XML files entering the [Publish Documents (Pweb)](/doxee-platform/docs/publish-documents-pweb-batch-workflow-task-reference) task must have different shipments.

Since the shipment is extrapolated from the output of the [Transform Files (DT)](/doxee-platform/docs/transform-files-dt-batch-workflow-task-reference) task, each file (one for each delivery task) must be produced by a different Transform Files (DT) task, or in any case each file must have a different Shipment ID.
